summary:
The Council:

* Reiterates its request to the Secretary-General to include child protection in his reports (para 14)
* Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report by 31 October 2004 on implementation of this resolution (para 15)
The Security Council:

 Requests the Secretary-General to provide in his reports:

(a) Information on violations of international law relating to the rights and protection of children, and other violations and abuses against children affected by armed conflict;

(b) Information on progress made regarding the action plan for a systematic and comprehensive monitoring and reporting mechanism;

(c) Best practices for disarmament, demobilization and reintegration (DDR) programmes;

Decides to remain actively seized of this matter.
